						               													<description>Ginga-X A solitaire space adventure game. &amp;#10;Players choose their ship from a list of pre-built ones, or build their own, then explore the star system! &amp;#10;Navigating the spaceways, battling alien ships, and gathering resources along the way, players must try to accomplish goals while balancing their ship's stats for maximum results.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each turn is divided into 5 steps:&amp;#10;1. Check for Alien Attack: (based on your ship's Stats, an enemy may appear!)&amp;#10;2. Check Risk: (the more 'unbalanced' your ship's Stats, the more dangerous your travels will become!  A perfectly balanced ship is considered to be in Harmony, and will yield amazing discoveries.&amp;#10;3. Move (optional): the ship may be moved to an adjacent sector or remain in its current position.&amp;#10;4. Check Sector FX: Compare the ship's Risk with the Sector's benefits/dangers!&amp;#10;5. Gather: the ship must gather as much of a chosen resource from the Sector as possible!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Ginga-X is fully expandable with new Star Systems and new Alien Ships, as well as new Pre-Built player ship options.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Berivov System includes the following 6 Sectors:&amp;#10;1. Planet Orpha&amp;#10;2. The Ruby Zone (field)&amp;#10;3. Planet Seirama&amp;#10;4. Planet Jenice&amp;#10;5, Berivov (pulsar star)&amp;#10;6. Planet Arkizon&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
